[{"id":"VR802600","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a point P midway between two vertical wires that are separated by a distance of 40 centimeters. The wire on the left carries a current of 2 amps toward the bottom of the page, and the wire on the right carries a current of 3 amps toward the top of the page.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR802600.g02.svg\"/></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Two current carrying wires are placed next to each other, as shown. One wire has a current of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2 amps\"><math alttext=\"2 amps\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></math></span></span> directed toward the bottom of the page and the other has a current of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"3 amps\"><math alttext=\"3 amps\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>3</mn><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></math></span></span> directed toward the top of the page. Point <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"P\"><math alttext=\"P\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi></math></span></span> is located directly in the middle of the two wires. What is the magnetic field at this point due to both wires?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR802600_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"5 times 10 raised to the negative 6 power tesla\"><math alttext=\"5 times 10 raised to the negative 6 power tesla\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>5</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>−</mo><mn>6</mn></mrow></msup><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">T</mi></math></span></span>, into the page</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span